{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σπάν-ις</b> [ᾰ], ἡ, <br /> <i>genitive</i> εως, <i>dative</i> ει, <i>Ionic dialect</i> ι:— <b>scarcity, dearth, lack</b>, τόλμης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 942; ἀνδρῶν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.31; ὕδατος 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 746b10, cf. LXX.Jdt.8.9; θηρίων 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 2.5.26; νεκύων “Anthologia Graeca” 9.53 (Nicodemus Epigrammaticus or 1st c.AD: Bassus, Lollius Epigrammaticus)\">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ σπάνις.. ἔχειν,= οὐ σπάνιον, <b>there is</b> no <b>lack</b>, no <b>difficulty</b>, in getting, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 1163 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὗ σ. ἀνδρὶ τυχεῖν which 'tis <b>rare</b> for a man to get, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 2.2753\">Refs</a>], compare 3577: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>dearth</b>, τροφὰς ἐν τῇ μεγάλῃ σ. παρέσχε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]3.687. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>unsatisfied need, want</b>, with <i>genitive</i>, ἐν σπάνι βύβλων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.58 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. σχεῖν τοῦ βίου <b>poverty</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1461; βίου 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 12; ἢν δέ του σπάνιν τιν᾽ ἴσχῃς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 506, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 678d; σ. τῶν ἀναγκαίων 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.1.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῇ τῶν χρημάτων σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.142; ἀργυρίου 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 19.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ.. σ. πρόχειρος εἰς τὸ δρᾶν κακά <b>want, poverty</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 157. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>craving</b>, defined as ἐπιθυμία ἀτελής, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Stoicorum Veterum Fragmenta” 3.97; ἐν σ. χρημάτων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.153, compare 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ παρρησίας” p.45 O. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G21113","accentedUnicode":"σπάνις","shortDef":"craving","mediumDef":"craving","stepGloss":"craving","stepTransliteration":"spanis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}